16/02/2004
KUWAIT CITY, Kuwait -- Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul on Saturday (14 February) called for the establishment of multilateral security mechanisms among the countries neighbouring Iraq. Gul urged fellow neighbours to take responsibility and show political determination to enhance regional security. He stressed that his proposal is in line with the decision made at the last meeting of the Organisation for Islamic Conference.
In other news, Turkish President Ahmet Necdet Sezer leaves Tuesday for Tehran where he will take part in the fourth meeting of the heads of states of developing countries.
On Sunday, meanwhile, about 40 people were arrested in Istanbul and Diyarbakir, Turkey for staging violent protests to mark the anniversary of the 1999 capture of Kurdish leader Abdullah Ocalan. (Anadolu Agency - 16/02/04; AFP, Anadolu Agency - 15/02/04)
